subsection.def:
committee
                    (委員會) includes any panel or sub-group
                established by the Council under section 17 of Schedule 1;

Council
                    (監警會) means the body corporate established by
                    section 4;

material
                    (材料) includes any document or record in any
                form and any article or substance;

observer
                    (觀察員) means a person appointed to be an
                observer under section 33;

Secretary-General
                    (秘書長) means the Secretary-General to the
                Council appointed under section 6(1);

paragraph.content:
the complainant is below the age of 16 years at the time when the complaint
                    or request for review (as the case may be) is made and the representative is his
                    relative or guardian;

subparagraph.content:
a guardian (as defined in section 2(1) of the Mental Health
                        Ordinance (Cap. 136)) of the complainant;
                        or

paragraph.content:
an adult who has an interest in the welfare of that person and is, in the
                    opinion of the Council, an appropriate person to be present at the interview;
                    or

must withdraw from the meeting during the discussion of the Matter if
                        so required by a majority of the other members present at the meeting;
                        and

must withdraw from the meeting during the discussion of the Matter if
                        so required by a majority of the other members present at the meeting;
                        and

the duty to submit an annual report, statement of accounts and
                        auditor’s report to the Chief Executive under section 30(1);
                        and
